<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06087296 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06087296 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SCHOOL; SPORT; REAL-ESTATE; INCREASE; NEIGHBORHOOD; OPPOSE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Neighbors of West Valley School in Sunnyvale say they fear plannedimprovements by the city to the athletic fields will draw people from out ofthe neighborhood and add to police, traffic and parking problems.;   Appearing last week at a city council meeting, the neighbors also asked that apublic phone proposed in the original $210,000 plan but deleted at the requestof Cupertino Union School District be included. The school is locatednorthwest of Highway 85 and Homestead Road.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Extra 2  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  CONCERNS VOICED OVER SCHOOL PLANS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Community News  </MEMO><TEXT>     Council members sought to allay fears of increased problems but agreed onthe need for a telephone in case someone using the park is injured.;    Thecouncil approved the master plan and agreed to write a letter to the schoolboard expressing &quot;deep concern&quot; about the need for a phone on the grounds. Theletter also will urge the district to screen its buildings from adjacentresidences with landscaping.;    The public telephone was in the originalmaster plan, but Cupertino Union School District asked that it be taken outbecause it might prove too attractive to students and become a nuisance toadministrators.;    While they were at it, neighbors complained that temporaryclassroom buildings across their fences, though not on the athletic fields,are too close. They asked for landscaping to screen them.;    &quot;I love kids,but I don't want them right in my back yard,&quot; one woman said.;    A 1989agreement between the city and the school district called for the city toimprove open space at five schools, increasing the amount of parkland that canbe used when school is out. The agreement gave ownership of nine acres nearOrtega Park and Ortega School to the city and provided for a $600,000 paymentto the district. The district agreed not to sell any school sites.;   Construction at Ortega and Stocklmeir schools should be finished soon. WestValley is to be improved by June 30, 1994. A master plan for Nimitz wasapproved in February and the work is to be done by June 30, 1992. CupertinoJunior High School will be improved in 1993.;    At West Valley, the city willbuild two softball fields, a soccer field and a jogging path, plant trees andshrubs around the edge, improve turf and irrigation systems and put up signs.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  LELAND JOACHIM, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910327  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  381  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday March 27, 199100087296,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>